{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "586c635e4f76790d", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 0, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/add-dir <path>`", "Add a working directory for file access during the current session. Most `.claude/` configuration is not discovered from the added directory. You can later resume the session from the added directory with `--continue` or `--resume`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "85f40d7aab12aa5f", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 1, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/agents`", "Manage agent configurations"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "bae575b245fa1aa1", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 2, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/autofix-pr [prompt]`", "Spawn a Claude Code on the web session that watches the current branch's PR and pushes fixes when CI fails or reviewers leave comments. Detects the open PR from your checked-out branch with `gh pr view`; to watch a different PR, check out its branch first. By default the remote session is told to fix every CI failure and review comment; pass a prompt to give it different instructions, for example `/autofix-pr only fix lint and type errors`. Requires the `gh` CLI and access to Claude Code on the web"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "5892ad53bfc4800a", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 3, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/batch <instruction>`", "Skill. Orchestrate large-scale changes across a codebase in parallel. Researches the codebase, decomposes the work into 5 to 30 independent units, and presents a plan. Once approved, spawns one background agent per unit in an isolated git worktree. Each agent implements its unit, runs tests, and opens a pull request. Requires a git repository. Example: `/batch migrate src/ from Solid to React`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "54336a5302bf45bb", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 4, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/branch [name]`", "Create a branch of the current conversation at this point. Switches you into the branch and preserves the original, which you can return to with `/resume`. Alias: `/fork`. When `CLAUDE_CODE_FORK_SUBAGENT` is set, `/fork` instead spawns a forked subagent and is no longer an alias for this command"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "673def505d5436cd", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 5, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/btw <question>`", "Ask a quick side question without adding to the conversation"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "ea83e7deedd0c8b6", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 6, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/chrome`", "Configure Claude in Chrome settings"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "df4aa795eb3aea5e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 7, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/claude-api [migrate|managed-agents-onboard]`", "Skill. Load Claude API reference material for your project's language (Python, TypeScript, Java, Go, Ruby, C#, PHP, or cURL) and Managed Agents reference. Covers tool use, streaming, batches, structured outputs, and common pitfalls. Also activates automatically when your code imports `anthropic` or `@anthropic-ai/sdk`. Run `/claude-api migrate` to upgrade existing Claude API code to a newer model: Claude asks which files to scan and which model to target, then updates model IDs, thinking configuration, and other parameters that changed between versions. Run `/claude-api managed-agents-onboard` for an interactive walkthrough that creates a new Managed Agent from scratch"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "967394fbac455128", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 8, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/clear`", "Start a new conversation with empty context. The previous conversation stays available in `/resume`. To free up context while continuing the same conversation, use `/compact` instead. Aliases: `/reset`, `/new`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "ef5aacfa8622c2d8", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 9, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/color [color|default]`", "Set the prompt bar color for the current session. Available colors: `red`, `blue`, `green`, `yellow`, `purple`, `orange`, `pink`, `cyan`. Use `default` to reset. When Remote Control is connected, the color syncs to claude.ai/code"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "ca4b8a2baf182262", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 10, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/compact [instructions]`", "Free up context by summarizing the conversation so far. Optionally pass focus instructions for the summary. See how compaction handles rules, skills, and memory files"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "7fa075f39723eb82", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 11, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/config`", "Open the Settings interface to adjust theme, model, output style, and other preferences. Alias: `/settings`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "9f42fb8c72bf4b3d", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 12, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/context`", "Visualize current context usage as a colored grid. Shows optimization suggestions for context-heavy tools, memory bloat, and capacity warnings"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "9964f57df2a96eef", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 13, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/copy [N]`", "Copy the last assistant response to clipboard. Pass a number `N` to copy the Nth-latest response: `/copy 2` copies the second-to-last. When code blocks are present, shows an interactive picker to select individual blocks or the full response. Press `w` in the picker to write the selection to a file instead of the clipboard, which is useful over SSH"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "a2ab890f70123f60", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 14, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/cost`", "Alias for `/usage`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "cfac597e49d9a6fc", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 15, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/debug [description]`", "Skill. Enable debug logging for the current session and troubleshoot issues by reading the session debug log. Debug logging is off by default unless you started with `claude --debug`, so running `/debug` mid-session starts capturing logs from that point forward. Optionally describe the issue to focus the analysis"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "10ed37663e11c591", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 16, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/desktop`", "Continue the current session in the Claude Code Desktop app. macOS and Windows only. Alias: `/app`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "36fe04d75c46fa2a", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 17, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/diff`", "Open an interactive diff viewer showing uncommitted changes and per-turn diffs. Use left/right arrows to switch between the current git diff and individual Claude turns, and up/down to browse files"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "e02c755849355d3e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 18, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/doctor`", "Diagnose and verify your Claude Code installation and settings. Results show with status icons. Press `f` to have Claude fix any reported issues"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "d58cce2fdc8ea4b8", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 19, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/effort [level|auto]`", "Set the model effort level. Accepts `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh`, or `max`; available levels depend on the model and `max` is session-only. `auto` resets to the model default. Without an argument, opens an interactive slider; use left and right arrows to pick a level and `Enter` to apply. Takes effect immediately without waiting for the current response to finish"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "651f7bfbfe7996e9", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 20, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/exit`", "Exit the CLI. Alias: `/quit`"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "aab40a9b088e4a99", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 21, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/export [filename]`", "Export the current conversation as plain text. With a filename, writes directly to that file. Without, opens a dialog to copy to clipboard or save to a file"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "60b4efe17715be4b", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 22, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/extra-usage`", "Configure extra usage to keep working when rate limits are hit"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "78d7fe8910338557", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 23, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/fast [on|off]`", "Toggle fast mode on or off"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "527b96e9f54e496b", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands.md#overview", "position": 24, "table_position": 0, "headers": ["command", "purpose"], "cells": ["`/feedback [report]`", "Submit feedback about Claude Code. Alias: `/bug`"]}
